ckoning (Willam Belli album)|The Wreckoning]]''\n|\n* Released: November 17, 2012\n* Label: [[Self-released]]\n* Format: [[Compact Disk|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Shartistry in Motion]]''\n|\n* Released: June 2, 2015\n* Label: Self-released\n* Format: Digital download\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Now That's What I Call Drag Music, Vol .1''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/now-thats-what-i-call-drag-music-vol-1/1438639119 |title=Now That's What I Call Drag Music, Vol .1 by Willam on iTunes |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=October 2018 |website=Apple Music | publisher = |access-date=October 25, 2018}}</ref><br>{{small|(alternatively known as ''Songs in the Key of Nope'')}}\n|\n* Released: October 26, 2018\n* Label: Self-released\n* Format: Digital download\n| 4\n|-\n| colspan=\"14\" style=\"font-size:90%\" | \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that failed to chart or was not released in that territory.\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard charts|US<br>Comedy<br>Digital]]<br><ref>{{cite web|title=Billboard Chart Archive|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=May 17, 2015|format=To access, type \"Willam\" in the artist bar, then select \"Comedy Digital Tracks\" in the chart name bar}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Trouble\"\n| rowspan=\"7\"|2012\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"9\"| ''The Wreckoning'' \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Chow Down]]\"<br>{{small|(featuring [[Detox (drag queen)|Detox]] & Vicky Vox)}}\n| 12\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Vagina Song\"\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Love You Like a Big Schlong\"\n| 25\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"She Doesn't Know\"\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Let's Have a KaiKai\"<br>{{small|(featuring [[Rhea Litr\u00e9]])}}\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Stand by Your Man#Drake Jensen and Willam Belli version|Stand by Your Man]]\"<br>{{small|(featuring [[Drake Jensen]])}}\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"RuPaulogize\"<br>{{small|(featuring [[Sharon Needles]])}}\n| rowspan=\"6\"| 2013\n| 14 \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Potential New Boyfriend]]\"\n| \u2014\n|-\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Boy Is a Bottom]]\"<br>{{small|(with [[DWV (group)|DWV]])}}\n| 6\n| rowspan=\"6\" {{N/A|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Silicone\"<br>{{small|(with DWV)}}\n| \u2014 \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Blurred Bynes\"<br>{{small|(with DWV)}}\n| 5 \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"That Christmas Song\"<br>{{small|(with DWV)}}\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Gaycation!\"<br>{{small|(with DWV)}}\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Hole Pic\"\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Only Anally\"\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''Shartistry in Motion''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"American Apparel Ad Girls\"<br>{{small|(with [[Courtney Act|Courtney]] and [[Alaska Thunderfuck 5000|Alaska]])}}\n| 10\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Dear Santa, Bring Me a Man\"<br>{{small|(with Courtney and Alaska)}}\n| \u2014\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Es Una Pasiva\"\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2015\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"3\"| ''Shartistry in Motion''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Ride for AIDS\"<br>{{small|(featuring Alaska)}}\n| 12\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Thick Thighs\"<br>{{small|(featuring [[Latrice Royale]])}}\n| 3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"I'm Not a Pearl\"\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Uck Foff\"\n| 2016\n|  12\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"AAA\"<br>{{small|(with Courtney and Alaska)}}\n| 2017\n|  2\n| ''Access All Areas''\n|-\n| colspan=\"14\" style=\"font-size:90%\" | \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that failed to chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n==Tours==\n*[[Access All Areas Tour]] {{small|(2017)}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tubefilter.com/2017/08/21/willam-alaska-courtney-act-aaa-girls-fullscreen/ |title=Drag Queens Willam, Alaska, Courtney Act Hit The Road For Fullscreen-Produced Tour |last1=Gutelle |first1=Sam |last2= |first2= |date=August 21, 2017 |website=[[Tubefilter]] | publisher = |accessdate=September 30, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n*{{cite book| title= Suck Less: Where There's a Willam, There's a Way | publisher = Grand Central Publishing | year = 2016 | isbn = 978-1455566198}}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n===NewNowNext Awards===\nBelli was nominated for his role on ''RuPaul's Drag Race'' at the fifth annual NewNowNext Awards which aired on Logo network on April 9, 2012. He lost to [[Nadia G.]] of ''[[Bitchin' Kitchen]]'' which airs on the [[Food Network Canada]] and the [[Cooking Channel]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2012 NewNowNext Awards|url=http://www.logotv.com/events/newnownext_awards/2012/categories/most-addictive-reality-star/|work=[[Logo TV]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013}}</ref> \n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|| 2012\n| Willam Belli ||  Most Addictive Reality Star || {{nom}}\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|www.willambelli.com}}\n*{{IMDb name|1316418|Willam Belli}}\n*{{Amg name|382680}}\n\n{{Willam Belli}}\n{{RuPaul's Drag Race}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Belli, Willam}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American bloggers]]\n[[Category:American drag queens]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:Gay actors]]\n[[Category:LGBT musicians from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:LGBT singers]]\n[[Category:LGBT YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:RuPaul's Drag Race contestants|Willam Belli]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Comedy YouTubers]]\n[[Category:American male bloggers]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Willam Belli \n| image = Dragcon3-SUN-3 (47942905293).jpg\n| caption= Willam Belli at ''[[RuPaul's DragCon LA|RuPaul's DragCon]]'' in 2019\n| birth_name = Willam Bart Belli\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|6|30|mf=yes}}<ref>{{cite news |author1=Gay Times |title=Happy birthday, Willam! |url=https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/41210/happy-birthday-willam/ |work=Gay Times |date=29 June 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Philadelphia]], [[Pennsylvania]], U.S.\n| residence = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| occupation = {{Flatlist |\n* [[Actor]]\n* [[drag queen]]\n* [[singer-songwriter]]\n* reality television personality\n* author\n* YouTuber}}\n| spouse = {{marriage|Bruce Bealke|2008}}\n| website = {{URL|http://www.willambelli.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Willam Bart Belli''' ({{IPAc-en|b|E|l|ai}}, born June 30, 1982), [[mononym]]ously known as '''Willam''', is an American actor, [[drag queen]], and recording artist. Willam came to prominence when he competed on the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 4)|fourth season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]'' in 2012, during which he became the first ever contestant to be disqualified from the series.\n\nBefore appearing on ''Drag Race'', Willam worked as an actor, most notably playing the recurring role of [[transgender]] woman [[Cherry Peck]] in [[Ryan Murphy (writer)|Ryan Murphy]]'s medical drama ''[[Nip/Tuck]]''. He has continued to perform in a variety of films, television series and web series, often in drag. In 2018, he appeared in the critically acclaimed film ''[[A Star Is Born (2018 film)|A Star Is Born]]'' directed by [[Bradley Cooper]].\n\nSince 2012, Willam has recorded three albums of comedy music, mostly consisting of parodies of popular songs. His second album, ''[[Shartistry in Motion]]'', debuted at number 1 on the Billboard [[Comedy Albums]] chart. Between 2012 and 2014, he recorded several songs as part of the group [[DWV (group)|DWV]] (alongside drag queens Vicky Vox and [[Detox Icunt|Detox]]), including the parodies \"[[Chow Down]]\" and \"[[Boy Is a Bottom]]\" whose music videos found [[viral video|viral success]]. Following the breakup of DWV, Willam formed another drag supergroup, [[the AAA Girls]], with [[Courtney Act]] and [[Alaska Thunderfuck]].\n\n==Early life==\nWillam Belli was born in Philadelphia. He is the younger of two children. Belli states he is of  Yugoslavian and Italian heritage.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://willambelli.tumblr.com/post/63505474820/is-willam-belli-your-given-name-if-so-where-did |title=Is Willam Belli your given name? |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=October 8, 2013 |website=[[Tumblr]] |publisher= |access-date=October 25, 2018}}</ref> He lived in Florida for middle school and high school.<ref name=\"dirty\">{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Brian Bowen|title=Willam Belli: How to Break the Rules |url=http://dirty-mag.com/v2/?p=12308|work=Dirty|accessdate=March 31, 2013|year=2012}}</ref> Belli's father worked at the [[Kennedy Space Center]]. His aunt is television director [[Mary Lou Belli]]. \n \nBelli was overweight when he was young but lost the extra pounds by becoming vegetarian before being emancipated at 16.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://willambelli.tumblr.com/post/139821364113/do-you-talk-to-your-family-know-after-getting |title=Do you talk to your family know after getting emancipated? |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=February 22, 2016 |website=Tumblr | publisher = |access-date=October 25, 2018}}</ref> Belli met his boyfriend Bruce, at nineteen. They were married on September 9, 2008.<ref>Sources pertaining to Belli's husband:\n*{{cite web |url=https://www.dragofficial.com/archives/qa-catching-up-with-willam-part-ii |title=Q&A: CATCHING UP WITH WILLAM (PART II) |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=February 2, 2014 |website=Drag Official | publisher = |access-date=October 25, 2018}}\n*{{cite web |url=https://willambelli.tumblr.com/post/22829640012/yourtone-seemsverypointed-willam-his-husband|title=Willam & his husband Bruce :\u2019) |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=May 11, 2012 |website=Tumblr | publisher = |access-date=October 25, 2018}}\n*{{cite web |url=https://willambelli.tumblr.com/post/136274678953/im-curious-you-say-your-husband-but-are-you|title=I'm curious, you say your husband but are you married?... |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=December 30, 2015 |website=Tumblr | publisher = |access-date=October 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2000\u20132008: Beginnings===\nBelli's first acting credit was as the role of a [[Male prostitution|street hustler]] named Bart Jaker on two episodes of ''[[The District]]'' (2002) and his first TV appearance was on an episode of the [[game show]] ''[[Street Smarts]]''.<ref name=\"dirty\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Willam Belli \u2013 IMDb|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1316418/|work=[[Internet Movie Database|IMDb]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013}}</ref> He later appeared in the TV series ''[[The District]]'', ''[[Boston Public]]'', ''[[Cold Case]]'', ''[[The Shield]]'', ''[[My Name Is Earl]]'' and most notably ''[[Nip/Tuck]]'' as the [[transgender]] character Cherry Peck. Throughout the 2000s he would go on to play small roles in many television shows. He also had a small role in the film  ''American Wedding''.\n\nIn 2008, Belli was featured on the single artwork for the song \"[[Breakin' Up (Rilo Kiley song)|Breakin' Up]]\" by [[Rilo Kiley]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Belli|first=Willam|title=Twitter / @willambelli: @KidsGoSplat yes I love Jenny ...|url=https://twitter.com/willambelli/statuses/276844304469741568|work=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=April 14, 2013|date=December 6, 2012}}</ref> He has also modeled as part of the [[Tranimal]] Master Class Workshop at the [[Machine Project]], which was photographed by [[Austin Young]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Tranimal Master Class Workshop on Vimeo|url=http://vimeo.com/48044519|work=[[Vimeo]]|accessdate=April 14, 2013|date=February 28, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132010: Drag career===\n[[File:Detox, William and Vicky Vox at Venue Nightclub in Houston, Tx. (8743144337).jpg|thumb|Belli with Vicky Vox and Detox Icunt|alt=]]\nBelli is a member of the band Tranzkuntinental, which made its debut at [[Roxy Theatre (West Hollywood)|The Roxy]] in 2009. The band was started by Charlie Paulson and Xander Smith and features drag queens [[Detox Icunt|Detox]], [[Kelly Mantle]], [[Rhea Litr\u00e9]], and Vicky Vox.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lecaro|first=Lina|title=L.A.'s A Drag: The Reign of Raja, Tranzkuntinental (and Adam Lambert) On Stage and the Dance Floor|url=http://blogs.laweekly.com/westcoastsound/2011/05/raja_tranzkuntinental_adam_lam.php|work=[[LA Weekly]]|accessdate=March 22, 2013|date=May 2, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Horbelt|first=Stephan|title=Scream Queens: Meet the Ghouls of Tranzkuntinental|url=http://www.frontiersla.com/Features/Highlights/Story.aspx?ID=1555194|work=[[Frontiers (magazine)|Frontiers]]|accessdate=March 22, 2013|date=October 13, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2011, he was featured in [[Rihanna]]'s music video \"[[S&M (song)|S&M]]\" along with [[Detox Icunt|Detox]] and [[Morgan McMichaels]] as back-up dancers.<ref>{{cite web|last=Belli|first=Willam|title=Season 2's Morgan McMichaels and season 4's Willam Belli with Rihanna for the \"S&M\" music video.|url=http://willambelli.tumblr.com/post/16603377985/fuckyeahrupaulsdragrace-season-2s-morgan|work=[[Tumblr]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=January 27, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2011\u20132012: ''RuPaul's Drag Race'' and further success===\n[[World of Wonder (production company)|World of Wonder]] contacted Willam's management asking for him to audition for the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 4)|fourth season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]''.<ref name=\"dirty\"/> In November 2011, [[Logo TV]] announced that Belli was among 13 contestants competing on the fourth season.<ref>{{cite web|last=Jones|first=Arnold Wayne|title=Logo announces cast for Season 4 of 'RuPaul's Drag Race'|url=http://www.dallasvoice.com/logo-releases-cast-list-season-4-rupauls-drag-race-1094450.html|work=[[Dallas Voice]]| publisher =Voice Publishing Company, Inc|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=November 15, 2011}}</ref> Fellow castmate [[Chad Michaels]] had competed with Belli in the California Entertainer of the Year Pageant in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|last=Addams|first=Calpernia|title=California EOY 2010 \u2013 The Recap |url=http://www.calpernia.com/diary/california-eoy-2010-the-recap/|work=[[Calpernia Addams|Calpernia.com]] |accessdate=March 30, 2013}}</ref> Belli won the main challenges in the episodes \"Float Your Bloat\" and \"Frenemies\", but was disqualified in the latter.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sava|first=Oliver|title=Float Your Boat|url=http://www.avclub.com/articles/float-your-boat,70257/|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=March 6, 2012}}</ref> In the episode \"Reunited\", Belli stated that his disqualification was due to [[conjugal visit]]s made by his husband in his hotel room,<ref>{{cite web|last=Stransky|first=Tanner|title=Controversial 'RuPaul's Drag Race' queen Willam explains disqualification: 'My husband was coming to bang me out' \u2013 UPDATED|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2012/05/01/rupauls-drag-race-willam-disqualified-banged-out/|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=May 1, 2012}}</ref> though by Belli's own account, the \"disqualification\" coincided with a previously booked off-Broadway engagement.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bruno|first1=Paul|title=Willam Belli: How to Break the Rules|url=http://dirty-mag.com/v2/?p=12308|website=dirty-mag.com| publisher =Dirty Magazine|accessdate=13 December 2014|date=May 2012|quote=I was doing a show off-broadway by that point!  It was called Jersey Shoresical.  In fact, two days after I got kicked off of drag race I was in Jersey Shoresical in New York, pretty convenient, huh?  And we won the Fringe Fest Audience Award.  It's almost like it was planned\u2026}}</ref> Belli used the publicity of his disqualification to release his single \"[[Chow Down]]\", which was a parody of [[Wilson Phillips]]' \"[[Hold On (Wilson Phillips song)|Hold On]]\" that addressed the 2012 [[Chick-fil-A same-sex marriage controversy]]. The song featured [[Detox Icunt|Detox]] and Vicky Vox.<ref name=\"huffingtonpost\">{{cite news|title=Willam Belli, RuPaul's Drag Race Star, Chats About Chick-fil-A and More|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/lady-bunny/willam-belli-chick-fil-a_b_1698119.html|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=March 30, 2013|author=[[Lady Bunny]]|date=July 24, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn March 12, 2012, he released his first single \"Trouble\", which was produced by [[RuPaul]]'s ''[[Red Hot (album)|Red Hot]]'' collaborator Tom Trujillo. The music video for the song was directed by porn director [[Chi Chi LaRue]] and premiered on [[Logo TV]].<ref name=\"dirty\"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Spargo|first=Chris|title=Willam Returns To Logo With 'Trouble' |url=http://www.newnownext.com/willam-trouble-music-video/11/2012/|work=[[Logo TV|New Now Next]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=November 25, 2012}}</ref>\nOn March 21, Belli released \"The Vagina Song\", a parody of \"[[Billionaire (song)|Billionaire]]\" by [[Travie McCoy]] featuring [[Bruno Mars]] as his third single, which had been previously uploaded to YouTube in 2010. The music video was directed by Michael Serrato,<ref name=\"queerty\">{{cite web|last=Debord|first=Matt|title=WATCH: What Willam Belli Would Do If He Was A Lady Down 'There'|url=http://www.queerty.com/watch-what-willam-belli-would-do-if-he-was-a-lady-down-there-20101027/|work=[[Queerty]]|accessdate=March 30, 2013 |date=October 27, 2010}}</ref> who also directed Belli's music video for \"[[Chow Down]]\".<ref name=\"huffingtonpost\"/>\n\nBelli released \"Love You Like a Big Schlong\" on April 29, 2012, which became a viral hit being viewed more than a million times on YouTube alone. Produced by [[Uncle Slam]], the song parodies \"[[Love You Like a Love Song]]\" by [[Selena Gomez & the Scene]]. The song was inspired by Belli's loss to 7-year-old [[Eden Wood]] in a [[lip sync]]ing contest during a segment of the 2012 [[NewNowNext Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Spargo|first=Chris |title=VIDEO: Willam, 'Love You Like A Big Schlong'|url=http://www.newnownext.com/willam-love-you-like-a-big-schlong-rupaul-drag-race/05/2012/|work=[[Logo TV|New Now Next]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=May 1, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2012, Belli was featured with [[country music]] artist [[Drake Jensen]] on a cover of [[Tammy Wynette]]'s \"[[Stand by Your Man#Drake Jensen and Willam Belli version|Stand by Your Man]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Video: Willam Goes Country With Help From Gay Artist Drake Jensen In \"Stand By Your Man\"|url=http://instinctmagazine.com/blogs/blog/video-willam-goes-country-with-help-from-gay-artist-drake-jensen-in-stand-by-your-man?directory=100011|work=[[Instinct (magazine)|Instinct]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=November 9, 2012}}</ref> That same month, Belli self-released his debut album ''[[The Wreckoning (Willam Belli album)|The Wreckoning]]'' via his website.<ref>{{cite web|last=Spargo|first=Chris |title=Go Buy Willam's Album, 'The Wreckoning'|url=http://www.newnownext.com/willam-album-the-wreckoning/11/2012/|work=[[Logo TV|New Now Next]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=November 18, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u20132013: Youtube Career, \"Boy Is a Bottom\", and DWV success===\nBeginning in December 2012, Belli began a YouTube series associated with thestylishvids titled, \"Willam's Beatdown\". A comedy segment involving insult humor and video reviews, the series would eventually be renewed for a second, third, fourth, fifth and sixth season that then premiered on Belli's self-titled channel. In January 2013, Belli would have his biggest viral hit with 20 million hits on YouTube alone, when he released \"[[Boy Is a Bottom]]\", featuring [[Detox Icunt|Detox]] and Vicky Vox, to coincide with the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 5)|fifth season]] premiere of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=This Boy Is A Bottom: Willam, Detox & Vicky Vox Return To Tackle Alicia Keys' 'Girl On Fire'|url=http://instinctmagazine.com/blogs/blog/this-boy-is-a-bottom-willam-detox-vicky-vox-return-to-tackle-alicia-keys-girl-on-fire?directory=100011|work=[[Instinct (magazine)|Instinct]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=January 28, 2013}}</ref> Its timing and the use of social media made it a very well received release. The song is a parody of \"[[Girl on Fire (song)|Girl on Fire]]\" by [[Alicia Keys]] and also features an altered version of the \"breakdown\" from \"[[My Lovin' (You're Never Gonna Get It)]]\" by [[En Vogue]].<ref>{{cite news|title='Boy Is A Bottom' Music Video Parody From Drag Queens Of 'Chow Down (At Chick-Fil-A)' (VIDEO)|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/01/28/boy-is-a-bottom-willam-vicky-vox-detox-drag-queens_n_2568983.html|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=January 28, 2013}}</ref> \"Boy Is a Bottom\" debuted at number six on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'''s Comedy Digital Songs, selling 3,000 downloads in its first week.<ref>{{cite web|last=Caulfied|first=Keith|title='RuPaul's Drag Race' Divas Debut in Top 10 on Billboard Dance Charts|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1538602/rupauls-drag-race-divas-debut-in-top-10-on-billboard-dance-charts |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=February 9, 2013|date=February 8, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn August 14, 2013, Belli was featured along with [[Shangela Laquifa Wadley|Shangela]], [[Detox Icunt|Detox]], [[Raven (drag queen)|Raven]], [[Morgan McMichaels]], Landon Cider, Shannel, and [[Courtney Act]], in [[Lady Gaga]]'s lyric video for her single \"[[Applause (Lady Gaga song)|Applause]]\".\n\nBelli's trio, including [[Detox Icunt|Detox]] and Vicky Vox, called [[DWV (group)|DWV]], officially split in June 2014 due to a personal conflict between the members.<ref name=\"Lance\">{{cite web|last1=Johnson|first1=Liam|title=US drag supergroup DWV split up|url=http://www.gaystarnews.com/article/us-drag-supergroup-dwv-split150614|website=gaystarnews.com|accessdate=7 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n===2014\u20132017: American Apparel, ''Shartistry in Motion'', first book, perfume and talk show===\nBelli then became an American Apparel Ad Girl alongside ''Drag Race'' alumni [[Courtney Act]] and [[Alaska Thunderfuck 5000]] which they supported with a single entitled, \"American Apparel Ad Girls\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.out.com/fashion/truman-says/2014/09/11/alaska-courtney-act-and-willam-belli-american-apparel|title=Exclusive: Alaska, Courtney Act, and Willam Belli Team Up With American Apparel|date=September 11, 2014| publisher =|accessdate=August 6, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1mhNedNUAa4|title=American Apparel Ad Girls with Courtney Act, Alaska 5000 and Willam #AAAgirls|first=|last=willam belli|date=September 30, 2014| publisher =|accessdate=August 6, 2017|via=YouTube}}</ref> They also released a second single together, \"Dear Santa, Bring Me a Man\" for the Christmas season.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/09/dear-santa-bring-me-a-man_n_6290536.html | work=Huffington Post | title=These Three Queens Have Just One Wish For Santa | date=December 9, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zudT4fu5cjc|title=Dear Santa, Bring Me A Man \u2013 Alaska, Courtney Act & Willam|first=|last=Courtney Act|date=December 8, 2014| publisher =|accessdate=August 6, 2017|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n\nOn January 13, he released a solo version of the ''DWV'' hit \"Boy Is a Bottom\", in Spanish, entitled, \"Es Una Pasiva\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/willam/photos/a.642759532403209.1073741828.635934403085722/915902075088952/?type=1&theater|title=Willam|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=August 6, 2017}}</ref> which went on to top the comedy iTunes chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/willam/photos/a.642759532403209.1073741828.635934403085722/917341178278375/?type=1&theater|title=Willam|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=August 6, 2017}}</ref> Belli self-released his sophomore studio album, ''[[Shartistry in Motion]]'', on June 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.out.com/theater-dance/2015/4/17/willam-belli-wants-get-thrown-out-her-own-show|title=Willam Belli Wants To Get Thrown Out of Her Own Show|date=April 17, 2015| publisher =|accessdate=August 6, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/shartistry-in-motion/id999417762|title=\"Shartistry in Motion\" by Willam on iTunes|website=iTunes|accessdate=August 6, 2017}}</ref>\n\nBelli released his first book ''Suck Less: Where There's a Willam, There's a Way'' in October 2016 through [[Grand Central Publishing]]. \nIn 2017, he released his first perfume collaboration with [[Xyrena]], Scented by Willam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newnownext.com/willams-new-perfume-smells-like-sandalwood-and-sex/02/2017/|title=Willam's New Perfume Smells Like Sandalwood And Sex| publisher =[[Logo TV]]|date=6 February 2017|accessdate=8 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn May 18, 2017, it was revealed that [[Fullscreen (company)|Fullscreen]] had ordered a talk show to be hosted by Belli. ''Suck Less'', billed as a weekly half-hour call-in show 'where Willam throws shade and shows how to slay the game of life in six-inch stilettos' is set to debut in the summer. Friends from Belli's everyday life, as well as some of his favorite drag queens are expected to put in guest appearances over the course of the 13-episode series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/willam-belli-fullscreen-talk-show-1202433682/|title=Drag Queen Star Willam Belli to Host Fullscreen Talk Show as Part of Gay-Pride Content Lineup|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=18 May 2017|accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===2018\u2013present: ''A Star is Born'' and other ventures===\nIn 2018, Willam appeared in the critically acclaimed film ''[[A Star Is Born (2018 film)|A Star Is Born]]''. Willam and fellow drag queen [[Shangela]] play queens working in a drag bar alongside [[Lady Gaga]]'s character Ally when she's discovered by famous country singer Jackson Maine, played by [[Bradley Cooper]]. Willam's character, Emerald, is a [[Dolly Parton]] impersonator who flirts with Jackson. The dialogue in his scenes was mostly improvised, including a memorable moment in which his character has Jackson autograph her silicone breastplate. Bradley Cooper, who also directed the film, said that Willam and Shangela \"blew his mind\" with their ad-libbing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/10/drag-races-shangela-and-willam-in-a-star-is-born.html|title=How Shangela and Willam Dragged Up A Star Is Born\n|publisher=Vulture|date=5 October 2019|accessdate=15 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Belli launched his own makeup line, Coverboy. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allure.com/story/willam-belli-coverboy-makeup-brand-products|title=Drag Race Star Willam Belli Launched His Own Makeup Brand, and the Sparkle Is Absurd|publisher=[[Allure (magazine)|Allure]]|date=14 September 2019|accessdate=15 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[American Pie: The Wedding]]''\n| Butch Queen\n|\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[The Last Shot]]''\n| Bus Stop Drag Queen\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''Screech of the Decapitated''\n| Marta \n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2006\n| ''Big Top''\n| Renee\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Unbeatable Harold]]''\n| Anita Boner\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Because I Said So (film)|Because I Said So]]''\n| Transsexual\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=5|2008\n| ''[[Defying Gravity (2008 film)|Defying G